claims:
Claims Claims 1. Device for providing a magnetic field for transfer of energy, the device comprising: A switching power supply for providing electrical power to the device; - An inductor coil for providing the alternating magnetic field; A resonance adjustment module for adjusting an inductor resonance frequency of an inductor resonance circuit comprising the inductor coil; A control module arranged to control the resonance adjustment module such that the inductor resonance frequency is substantially constant. 2. Device according to claim 1, further comprising a power factor correction module having an adjustable power factor correction, wherein the control module is arranged to control the power factor correction module such that the power factor in the circuit is substantially constant and preferably substantially equal to one. 3. Device according to claim 1 or 2, wherein the resonance adjustment module comprises an adjustable capacitance provided in series with the inductor coil. 4. Device according to claim 3, wherein the adjustable capacitance comprise a switched capacitor bank. 5. Device according to any of the claims 2 to 4, wherein the power factor correction module comprises an adjustable capacitance 

 provided parallel to the inductor coil and, to the extent dependent on claim 3, parallel to the adjustable capacitance. 6. Device according to claim 5 to the extent dependent on claim 2, wherein the power factor correction module is provided parallel to the resonance adjustment module. 7. Device according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the switching power supply comprises a voltage source and a first resonance bandpass filter. 8. Device according to claim 7, wherein the loaded quality factor of at least one and preferably all of the resonance circuits is 2.5 or higher. 9. Device according to claim 7 or 8, wherein the first resonance bandpass filter comprises a capacitance and an inductance provided in series with the voltage source. 10. Device according to any of the claims 7 to 9, wherein the switching power supply further comprises a pulse width modulation capable voltage source. 11. Parking place comprising the device according to any of the preceding claims, wherein the inductor coil comprises windings provided around a substantially vertically oriented axis. 12. Device for receiving energy by means of an alternating magnetic field, the device comprising: An inductor coil for receiving energy from a magnetic field; 

 A resonance adjustment module for adjusting an inductor resonance frequency of an inductor resonance circuit comprising the inductor coil; A terminal for a load for absorbing received energy; and - A control module arranged to control the resonance adjustment module such that the inductor resonance frequency is substantially constant. 13. Device according to claim 12, wherein the resonance adjustment module comprises a switched capacitor bank. 14. Device according to claim 13, wherein the switched capacitor bank is provided parallel to the inductor coil. 15. Electrical vehicle comprising the device according to any of the claims 12 to 14, wherein the coil is provided near an outer part of the vehicle and the inductor coil comprises windings provided around a substantially vertically oriented axis.
